  "source_notes": "Sy Scholfield quotes from \"Roamer: Hard-working poet Hattie had so many strings to her bow,\" Belfast Newsletter, 16 March 2016 [http://www.newsletter.co.uk/news/features/roamer-hard-working-poet-hattie-had-so-many-strings-to-her-bow-1-7278083]: \"Born at 2.10 am on Monday, November 1, 1926, Hattie was 'a real surprise' said son John. Her mother Eva had delivered baby Betty (who died last year) a few hours before midnight and didn’t know that twin sister Hattie was waiting to embark on her childhood in Ballycolman!\"\\nBallycolman is now part of Strabane.\\n\\n\\n",
